These deportees, among 104 Indians sent back by the US, included 13 women and eight children. They were taken to their native places in Gujarat in police vehicles, with tension and apprehension evident as they exited the airport.
title: Flight which crash-landed dreams: Debts, social scrutiny await US returnees in Gujarat
